ratings.comment: This class can be tough and the way she presents class is difficult. She mostly just reads off of her notes and answer sheets. Class isn't the most engaging. The Lab isn't hard if you work with someone and help eachother.

Super nice professor. Definitely one of the more confusing courses I've taken and she did a great job explaining the content. Her lectures are engaging and she provides study guides for exams that are pretty similar to the actual test. Prof Fulvio made a class that I was nervous to take before this year into one of my favorites this semester.

She is just overall a very kind person. I felt like her lectures were clear and helpful, even with the most difficult topics. She also teaches via chalkboard rather than slides which makes it easier to pay attention. I would recommend her 210 class to anyone, especially those who are nervous about statistics.

Jackie is an awesome teacher! She is super nice and she makes the class enjoyable. She wants every student to succeed and gives many opportunities for extra credit. I would HIGHLY recommend taking a Psychology class with her.
Take her class! Jackie gives great lectures so make sure to attend. The homework and practice exams are a great help to the finals

She makes this class incredibly easy! If you need to take this class take it with Jackie. It is clear that she wants to help her students and she tries to make this relatively boring information interesting. She explains everything very thoroughly, if you do not like math and need to take PSYCH 210 take it with Jackie!

If you have to take this class, definitely take it with Jackie! She makes a class that could be incredibly tough way easier to understand. Email her any question about the class and she responds almost instantly. Review packets are exactly like the exam. If you actually attend her lectures, you will do fine in the class.
Lectures are very clear and helpful. Go to lecture, do the practice problems  good grade.

If you are to take Psych 210, take it with Jackie Fulvio! Her lecture is super clear and the practice exams are highly related with the real exams. The exams contain huge amount of questions, so get enough practice! But I bet you can't get someone explaining stat clearer than Fulvio.

Jackie is a great professor! Her lectures are super clear, and she is really helpful in her office hours if you have a question. The class is relatively easy, therefore if you want an A you can't lose easy points on homework because the curve will not work in your favor. For exams, complete the online reviews that she posts and go to lecture!!

Professor Fulvio is a great professor. She's very enthusiastic about what she does and makes lecture engaging. She explains the material well and makes any confusing concepts easier to understand. The exams are extremely reflective of the lectures, homework, reviews, etc. I highly recommend this class with Professor Fulvio.

She tries very hard to explain the materials clearly. She really cares about students to get the materials correct. Very helpful in lecture and if you are confused, you can look up the textbook. Materials are not that difficult, but you need to get things straight. she gives a lot of practices, so if you do those, you will be good.

She is amazing! She explains the material extremely well and the best part about her class is she actually wants you to learn and makes sure you understand the concepts. Her exams are fair and she doesn't assign a lot of homework. She answers questions easily and made class fun! Jackie is an awesome professor!

Jackie was very nice, helpful and passionate about the subject. The material is a little tough if you don't like numbers, but it stacks onto itself, so if you get the core concepts, you'll do fine. Only problem is she abbreviates a lot of her notes, so you need to pay close attention to what she says while writing.
Super nice and helpful. Exams are really long and require you to put all formulas! Attendance isn't needed but helps a lot. Didn't really even touch my book

While this class itself isn't the easiest material, Professor Fulvio breaks it down in a way that is easy to understand. She is incredibly helpful, and answers her email questions really quickly which I always enjoy. Tests are fair and there are homework assignments. As long as you keep up in the book you will do fine
The material is hard, but prof. Fulvio made it as enjoyable as it could be. Would take this class again if I could.
